2
}}}
}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 he must appoint two examining physicians and schedule a competency hearing. The hearing is to the court alone, without a jury. The examining physicians\rquote  testimony and \u8216\'3fother evidence\u8217\'3f may be adduced on the issue of incompetency. If the court finds the defendant \u8216\'3fhas not comprehension sufficient to understand the proceedings and make his defense,\u8217\'3f trial is delayed or continued and the defendant is remanded to the state department of mental health to be confined in an \u8216\'3fappropriate psychiatric institution.\u8217\'3f The section further provides that \u8216\'3f(w)henever the defendant shall become sane\u8217\'3f the superintendent of the institution shall certify that fact to the court, and the court shall order him brought on to trial. The court may also make such an order sua sponte. There is no statutory provision for periodic review of the defendant\rquote s condition by either the court or mental health authorities. Section 9\u8212\'3f1706a by its terms does not accord the 
}
