*741
}
}
{\f2 \strike0 \ul0 \b0 \sa0 \sb0 \fs20 \cf1 \i0 
 defenses, not including lack of criminal responsibility, could be raised by defense counsel on the basis of which the court might quash the indictment. Some States have statutory provisions permitting pretrial motions to be made or even allowing the incompetent defendant a trial at which to establish his innocence, without permitting a conviction.
}
{\f2 \b0 \fs16 \cf1 \i0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_footnoteReference_B031301972127136_ID}{\*\bkmkend co_footnoteReference_B031301972127136_ID}
